<p>Form controls are used to style and standardize common form elements
such as inputs, <code>select</code>s, and <code>textarea</code>s. These
utilities provide accessible, responsive, and theme-aware UI elements
with support for validation, focus styling, and dark mode.</p>
<h3 id="doc-basic-markup">Basic Markup</h3>
<pre class="html"><code>&lt;label for=&quot;example&quot; class=&quot;form-label&quot;&gt;Your name&lt;/label&gt;
&lt;input type=&quot;text&quot; id=&quot;example&quot; class=&quot;form-control&quot; placeholder=&quot;Enter your name&quot;&gt;</code></pre>
<p>Use <code>.form-label</code> for consistent label spacing, and
<code>.form-control</code> for styled form elements.</p>
